                  <join result="offencePlace" targOrder="Y" targets="t18280410-187-off1004 t18280410-187-crimeloc1006"></join>. On Sunday evening, the 23d of March, between seven and eight o'clock, I had been serving in my shop; I went out of the shop door to the private door, and met the prisoner coming out of the passage; I took hold of her, and asked what she had got; she dropped a plate which broke, and said, "It is from real hunger" - I took her back, and found these other articles in her pocket; they had been taken from my washhouse - she threatened to destroy herself.(Property produced and sworn to.)</p>
